The Eurovision Song Contest is just around the corner and this year, it's taking place in Malmo, Sweden.

You can find out all about the event right here.

The UK's entry for 2024 is Olly Alexander who'll be performing his song, Dizzy.

But how's he feeling ahead of the big night, where he'll perform in front of 200 million people!

De-Graft sat down with him to find out all about his preparation for the competition.

The Eurovision Song contest Grand Final will be shown on BBC One and iPlayer on Saturday 11 May.

"As for the setlist, it's a special curated mix of my biggest hits and also some new music that I can't wait for the fans to hear. I've always been passionate about my performances, and I think this one is going to be truly something special. Plus, I'm honored to be sharing the stage with such an incredible lineup of artists, it's going to be a fantastic show for everyone involved."

"And to add an extra layer of excitement to the event, I'm also going to be bringing out some special surprise guests to join me on stage for a few of the songs, it's going to be a memorable night to say the least!"

"I think you're really going to love the ones I've selected, not only are they talented in their own right, but they also share a deep connection to the legacy of our music and will bring a level of energy and passion to the performance that will get the whole crowd on their feet and singing along!"
